    "where R κ is the spatial neighborhood matrix defined by Besag et al. (1991) considering that two areas are neighbors if they share a common border, I A is the identity matrix of size A × A, R γ is determined by the temporal structure matrix of a first order random walk (see Rue and Held, 2005, p. 95) and Q χ is the structure matrix that represents any of the four spatio-temporal interaction types proposed by Knorr-Held (2000).",
